<TITLE> Indian strike halts trade through land ports </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 27 (bdnews24.com)  Export and import through the Benapole and Akhaura land ports were suspended on Tuesday due to a dawn-to-dusk strike in the neighbouring Indian state of Tripura. bdnews24.com Benapole correspondent reported that a large number of good-laden trucks were stranded on both sides of the border. The strike was imposed by 13 political parties and was effective from 6am to 6pm. Kartik Chatterjee, the secretary of Petropole C&F Staff Welfare Association, said the workers went strike to protest an increase in prices in India. He said no goods could move through the border. Ashrafu Udin, Benapole's customs superintendent, said trade through the port would be normal from Wednesday. bdnews24.com Brahmanbaria correspondent reported that the Indian strike also halted trade through the Akhaura land port. Many trucks load with goods were waiting at the port. bdnews24.com/
